# Abdi Adama School IMS Implementation Plan (Updated)

This document is the current implementation plan for the Abdi Adama School Integrated Management System (IMS), aligned with the latest direction.

## 1. Scope Clarification (Critical)

- Monthly student fee collection logic is out of scope for this system.
- The school already uses a bank-side product for recurring/monthly fee processing.
- The IMS should only support fixed registration/enrollment fee workflows where explicitly required.

## 2. Delivery Strategy

- Build in production-oriented phases with working deliverables every week.
- Prioritize data integrity, role-based access, and operational automation first.
- Keep modules loosely coupled so post-launch features (LMS + AI) can scale without rewrites.

## 3. Phase Roadmap

## Phase 1: Multi-Campus and Data Foundation (Week 1)

### Goal
Establish the single source of truth and dual-admin hierarchy.

### Workstreams

#### Cloud Infrastructure

- Deploy production environment on Hahu Cloud for local performance and ETB cost-efficiency.
- Configure PostgreSQL with a schema that tags every core record with a unique Branch ID:
  - Student
  - Fee-related registration records
  - Staff
  - Operational logs
- Enable SSL encryption across all environments.
- Set up automated daily backups with restore verification.

#### Student Information System (SIS) and Vault

- Build comprehensive student profile fields for:
  - Bio-data
  - Emergency contacts
  - Medical history
  - Parent/guardian details
- Implement encrypted document vault logic for:
  - Birth certificates
  - Transcripts
- Enforce hard validation rule: reject any attachment above 2MB.

#### Registration and Access Control

- Build enrollment page for admins to manage and collect fixed fees for:
  - New students
  - Returning students
- Configure two-tier RBAC:
  - School Owner: global access across all branches
  - Branch Director: access only to assigned branch
- Create accountant-specific view:
  - Financial data access only for accountancy roles
  - Bank statement auditing restricted to accountancy roles

### Phase 1 Deliverables

- Production cloud environment on Hahu Cloud
- Branch-aware PostgreSQL schema
- SSL + daily backup automation
- SIS profile module
- Encrypted document vault with 2MB file cap
- Enrollment admin page (fixed fee handling only)
- Owner/Director dual-admin RBAC
- Accountant-only finance auditing workspace

## Phase 2: Teacher Workstation and Communication (Week 2)

### Goal
Automate classroom flow, attendance, and parent engagement.

### Workstreams

#### Teacher Workstation

- Build teacher portal/dashboard with controlled entry after admin approval.
- Limit class and section visibility to assigned teaching load.
- Implement dynamic rosters that auto-fetch students based on teacher schedule.
- Build grade entry interfaces for:
  - Quizzes
  - Assignments
  - Tests
  - Finals

#### Attendance and SMS Integration

- Integrate ZKTeco fingerprint devices into staff attendance module.
- Connect USB GSM modem for SMS dispatch pipeline.
- Wire teacher dashboard absence action to instant SMS alert script for families.

#### Scheduling and Resource Management

- Deploy conflict-free timetable engine for classes and teachers.
- Implement resource allocation tracking for labs and computer hubs.
- Prevent double-booking of shared resources.

### Phase 2 Deliverables

- Teacher workstation with approval-based access
- Dynamic class rosters and grade entry workflows
- ZKTeco attendance integration (staff)
- GSM modem SMS trigger pipeline
- Real-time absence alert workflow
- Conflict-free timetable module
- Resource booking and double-booking prevention

## Phase 3: Finance, Assets, and Grading Engine (Week 4)

### Goal
Generate audit-ready operations and print-ready academic intelligence.

### Workstreams

#### Automated Grading Engine

- Implement backend calculation engine to aggregate subject scores.
- Compute totals, averages, and GPA based on configured grading rules.
- Apply student privacy filtering so each student sees only their own results.
- Finalize one-click print-ready outputs:
  - Progress reports
  - Transcripts

#### Financial Auditing and Assets

- Build bank statement intake and reconciliation UI against school records.
- Link biometric attendance to payroll computation:
  - Salary calculation
  - Tax deductions
- Implement digital stock tracking for accessories and uniforms.
- Add low-stock alerting for critical items.

#### Final Handover and Training (Last Week)

- Finalize executive dashboard for school owner:
  - Total revenue
  - Student counts
  - Teacher attendance across branches
- Finalize transport route mapping so families can view:
  - Assigned bus
  - Assigned driver
- Conduct on-site training for:
  - Directors
  - Accountants
  - Teachers
- Conclude with final service agreement sign-off.

### Phase 3 Deliverables

- Grading computation engine + privacy-safe student results
- Print-ready report cards and transcripts
- Reconciliation and financial auditing tools
- Biometric-linked payroll calculations
- Inventory and low-stock monitoring
- Executive cross-branch dashboard
- Parent-facing transport assignment visibility
- Completed stakeholder training and handover package

## Phase 4: Future Layer (Post-Launch)

### Goal
Scale the platform with advanced academic and predictive features.

### Workstreams

- Complete LMS frontend integration for:
  - Lesson plans
  - Digital repositories
- Start AI early-warning model training to flag students at risk.
- Expand to headquarters-level controls for additional branches.

### Phase 4 Deliverables

- Functional LMS layer
- Early-warning analytics baseline
- Expanded multi-campus governance tooling

## Phase 5: Exams and Grading (Assessment Integrity)

### Goal
Deliver secure virtual assessments with role-controlled exam operations and reliable submission handling at scale.

### Virtual Assessment and Integrity Engine

- Teacher Module: Subject-specific question bank supporting multiple-choice (MCQ) formatting and exam batching (e.g., "G12 4th Model").
- Admin Command Center: Centralized control for exam scheduling, duration management, and invigilator assignment.
- Student Secure Environment:
  - Tab-Lock Technology: Detects and logs any attempt to switch tabs or minimize the browser.
  - Dynamic Navigation: Allows students to move freely between questions while providing a collapsible live countdown.
  - Auto-Submit Protocol: Ensures exams are closed and saved precisely when time expires, or upon manual submission.
  - Persistence: Local-state saving to protect student progress against local connectivity issues.

### Technical Note for Nexora

Since the platform is hosted on HahuCloud, the Submit_Exam API endpoint must be optimized for burst traffic. When many students submit at the same time, the system must avoid duplicate writes and DB overload.

- Optimization requirement:
  - On "Finish", immediately show a "Submitting..." loader.
  - Disable the submit button until the API responds.
  - Enforce idempotent submit handling server-side to prevent repeated inserts from multi-click attempts.

## 4. Cross-Phase Technical Rules

- Every domain record must include Branch ID where branch scoping is relevant.
- RBAC checks must be enforced server-side, not UI-only.
- All sensitive document storage must be encrypted.
- Backup jobs must run daily and be monitored.
- Audit logs must track sensitive financial and academic actions.
- File uploads must enforce the 2MB limit consistently across API and UI.

## 5. Out-of-Scope (For Now)

- Monthly recurring student fee engine.
- Replacing the bank product currently handling monthly fees.
- Non-critical experimental integrations not listed in the five phases.

## 6. Immediate Execution Sequence

1. Lock Week 1 infrastructure and branch-aware schema.
2. Implement SIS + encrypted vault + RBAC in parallel tracks.
3. Deliver teacher workstation, attendance, and SMS automation in Week 2.
4. Build grading engine, finance reconciliation, payroll, and inventory in Week 4.
5. Run final training, handover, and sign-off.
6. Start post-launch LMS and AI expansion.
